-- S. African Union Calls for Nationalization, Sunday Times Reports
-- B y   R o b e r t   B r a n d
-- 2012-06-03T09:16:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-03/s-african-union-calls-for-nationalization-sunday-times-reports.html
The National Union of Metalworkers,
 South Africa ’s second-biggest labor union, called for the
nationalization of “all strategic economic assets” including
banks, mines and energy companies, the  Sunday Times  reported,
citing Irvin Jim, the group’s general secretary.  The union, which is holding its national congress this
week, also called for the protection of property rights to be
removed from the constitution to allow nationalization without
compensation, the Johannesburg-based newspaper cited Jim as
saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Robert Brand in  Cape Town  at 
 rbrand9@bloomberg.net   To contact the editors responsible for this story: Gavin Serkin
at   gserkin@bloomberg.net . 